
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `logger` baraye ezafe kardan payam be log file system estefade mishavad. In dastoor bishtar baraye sabte etela'at dar morede rooydad-ha, khata-ha, ya digar payam-haye mohem be kar miravad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `logger "payam"` --> 💬 Sabte yek payam sade dar log file.
    🔹 `logger -p priority "payam"` --> 🚨 Sabte payam ba ahamiyat moshakhas (mesle error, warning).  Ahamiyat-ha mesle `emerg`, `alert`, `crit`, `err`, `warning`, `notice`, `info`, `debug` hastand.
    🔹 `logger -t tag "payam"` --> 🏷️ Ezafe kardane yek tag be payam log shode.  In tag baraye peygiri va joda kardane payam-ha az manba' haye mokhtalef mofeed ast.
    🔹 `logger -f file` --> 📁 Sabte matn az yek file be log.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ logger "Salam donya!"

    🔹 Sabte payam "Salam donya!" dar log file system.

    $ logger -p err -t myscript "Yek khata rokh dad!"

    🔹 Sabte payam "Yek khata rokh dad!" ba ahamiyat 'error' va tag 'myscript' dar log.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ logger -p warning "Faza-ye disk kam ast."

    🔹 Sabte payam "Faza-ye disk kam ast." ba daraje ahamiyat 'warning' dar log file.  In komak mikonad ke masoolan system az mozo' agah shavand.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `logger` command is used to make entries in the system log file. It is primarily used to record information about events, errors, or other important messages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `logger "message"` --> 💬 Logs a simple message to the log file.
    🔹 `logger -p priority "message"` --> 🚨 Logs a message with a specified priority level (e.g., error, warning).  Priority levels include `emerg`, `alert`, `crit`, `err`, `warning`, `notice`, `info`, `debug`.
    🔹 `logger -t tag "message"` --> 🏷️ Adds a tag to the logged message. This tag is useful for tracking and distinguishing messages from different sources.
    🔹 `logger -f file` --> 📁 Logs the content of a file to the log.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ logger "Hello world!"

    🔹 Logs the message "Hello world!" to the system log file.

    $ logger -p err -t myscript "An error occurred!"

    🔹 Logs the message "An error occurred!" with the 'error' priority and the 'myscript' tag.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ logger -p warning "Disk space is low."

    🔹 Logs the message "Disk space is low." with a 'warning' priority to the log file. This helps system administrators become aware of the issue.
